2 reviews for Shirley Brian Color Changing Cotton Yarn – Page 1





Rated 5 out of 5

Jennifer Kimball – February 23, 2016

Picked up this yarn when I went into Rosehaven for needles. Started the Mariner pattern and am loving the gradual colour change and the ever increasing number of stitches. Working on my first “knot” row now and finding it fairly simple but effective. Converted the pattern into an excel spreadsheet for ease of making. There are quite a few repeats of rows one and two and I find it easier to tick off the rows rather than write it down. Pics soon on ravelry.








Rated 5 out of 5

Evelyne Sawyer – May 12, 2016

Really enjoyed doing this Mariner pattern- quite simple and especially the blocking made the finished piece so attractive! would do it again









